    <p>AC­TOR LEAKS EX­PLICIT PHOTO: ST Face­book users praised the way fans and Cap­tain Amer­ica ac­tor Chris Evans be­haved af­ter he ac­ci­den­tally leaked a pic­ture of a man’s pri­vate parts on In­sta­gram. Fans flooded Twit­ter with whole­some pic­tures, like the star with his dog, to drown out the ex­plicit pic­tures. He broke his si­lence by tweet­ing of the United States pres­i­den­tial elec­tion: “Now that I have your at­ten­tion... vote Nov 3rd!!!” ST Face­book user Martin Lee said: “Bril­liant, he’s turned what could have been a huge neg­a­tive into some­thing that’s more im­por­tant to dis­cuss and to do in cur­rent af­fairs.”</p>
    <p>LONG NAPS ‘LINKED TO ILL HEALTH’: Read­ers woke up and smelled the cof­fee when they read about naps lasting over an hour be­ing pos­si­bly linked to ill­ness. Lots of ST Face­book users shared the re­port and poked fun at it too. Ram Tor­res joked: “59 minute nap, 90% sur­vival rate. 60 minute nap, 50% sur­vival rate. 61 minute nap, 10% sur­vival rate.”</p>


